14:18.959 --> 14:21.194
We'll take ours to go.

14:21.228 --> 14:23.496
That bag's just chopsticks
and napkins.

14:23.530 --> 14:25.232
Please, you're being crazy.

14:25.265 --> 14:26.599
I only see my son
every two weeks.

14:26.633 --> 14:29.369
And who's fault is that?
[ Whispers ] Asshole!

14:29.402 --> 14:34.141
I think this is the slippery
shrimp and orange chicken.

14:34.174 --> 14:36.543
You can be a real bitch
sometimes, you know that?

14:36.576 --> 14:39.146
Sometimes I wish
I never met you!

14:39.179 --> 14:41.114
[ Engine starts ]

14:41.148 --> 14:44.051
Hey, Daddy didn't mean to yell.
That's not who I am.

14:44.084 --> 14:47.320
Uh...I'll see you in a couple
weeks, okay, buddy?

14:47.354 --> 14:49.422
Hey, I'm gonna practice
that crossbow!

14:51.391 --> 14:53.160
[ Vehicle departs ]

14:56.596 --> 15:01.301
Uh...come on inside.
Checkbook's in the house.

15:01.334 --> 15:04.304
[ Crickets chirping,
dog barking in distance ]

15:04.337 --> 15:05.672
How's the methadone?

15:05.705 --> 15:08.075
It's not as good
as heroin.

15:08.108 --> 15:09.509
What the hell happened?

15:09.542 --> 15:11.211
He attacked me with a wrench.
You were right.

15:11.244 --> 15:14.447
I never should have let
the owner of the house in.

15:14.481 --> 15:15.648
[ Exhales sharply ]

15:15.682 --> 15:17.517
I think he's headed
to a bikini bar.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.252
I'm sending backup. Don't go
there until they arrive.

15:19.286 --> 15:21.488
Dad, I can do this alone.

15:21.521 --> 15:23.957
[ Cellphone clicks ]

15:23.991 --> 15:25.625
What do you mean you're
"Giving me the club?"

15:25.658 --> 15:27.060
I'm leaving the country.

15:27.094 --> 15:28.595
Rent's due on the first
of the month.

15:28.628 --> 15:30.130
Oh, and the beer distributor's
been giving me a discount

15:30.163 --> 15:31.598
'cause I blew him
in a parking lot,

15:31.631 --> 15:34.134
but you'll probably have
to start paying full price.

15:34.167 --> 15:35.368
Unless he swings both ways.

15:35.402 --> 15:37.504
It's possible.
He did cry afterwards.

15:40.640 --> 15:42.142
Yeah, I'm gonna
pay full price.

15:42.175 --> 15:44.177
But do I have to keep
it a bikini bar?

15:44.211 --> 15:45.678
'Cause I always thought we could
do better as a sports bar.

15:45.712 --> 15:47.080
Do whatever you want.

15:47.114 --> 15:48.982
I'll be making love
on a beach.

15:51.218 --> 15:53.987
[ Door opens ]

15:58.658 --> 16:00.527
Aw, nuts.

16:00.560 --> 16:03.363
This'll be a lot easier
if you just tell me where he is.

16:03.396 --> 16:05.532
I told you.
I don't know where he is.

16:05.565 --> 16:07.467
[ Sighs ]

16:07.500 --> 16:10.037
[ Car door opens ]

16:10.070 --> 16:11.238
[ Engine starts ]

16:11.271 --> 16:13.173
He couldn't have gotten far.

16:13.206 --> 16:14.641
I'll be back.

16:14.674 --> 16:16.409
The next time you see
your boyfriend,

16:16.443 --> 16:18.778
you'll be handcuffed to each
other on your way to jail.

16:18.811 --> 16:20.313
[ Gears shift ]

16:22.615 --> 16:23.783
Wait, wait!

16:23.816 --> 16:25.485
[ Tires screech ]

16:27.554 --> 16:30.257
[ Brakes squeal ]

16:30.290 --> 16:32.025
Did he really tell you
he was my boyfriend?

16:34.061 --> 16:35.295
[ Gears shift ]

16:53.746 --> 16:55.748
Pedro:
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

16:55.782 --> 16:57.450
What the hell
just happened?

16:57.484 --> 16:59.352
You're surprised, right?

16:59.386 --> 17:01.121
See, as soon as you got me
thinking this could be a movie,

17:01.154 --> 17:03.790
I left out some stuff to make
the ending more unexpected.

17:03.823 --> 17:06.093
Ah, a twist!

17:06.126 --> 17:07.460
I love a good twist.

17:07.494 --> 17:09.529
Of course you do.
Everyone loves a twist.

17:11.864 --> 17:14.734
Are you going to tell me
what you left out?

17:14.767 --> 17:16.136
Yeah, in a sec.

17:16.169 --> 17:19.606
Everyone loves suspense, too.

17:25.845 --> 17:28.115
[ Coughing ] Okay!

17:28.148 --> 17:30.617
Here's what I left out.

17:30.650 --> 17:32.752
Blake.

17:32.785 --> 17:35.722
Oh, my God. Okay.

17:35.755 --> 17:37.190
Andrew: Wait!

17:37.224 --> 17:38.491
Jessica, wait!

17:40.260 --> 17:42.795
[ Exhaling ]

17:42.829 --> 17:45.398
Fine. If you got to shoot me,
then shoot me.

17:45.432 --> 17:48.168
At least it'll be quicker than
whatever the cartel does to me.

17:54.674 --> 17:56.543
Take me with you.

17:56.576 --> 17:57.877
What?

17:57.910 --> 18:00.413
You said the ending
of my poem was too sad.

18:00.447 --> 18:02.282
Help me write a new one.

18:02.315 --> 18:04.784
"Riding into the sunset
with my brand-new honey

18:04.817 --> 18:07.620
and a suitcase full
of some drug dealer's money"

18:07.654 --> 18:09.289
is a much better rhyme than

18:09.322 --> 18:11.558
"Sitting all alone
eating Lean Cuisine,

18:11.591 --> 18:14.827
watching 'Magic Mike'
while I diddle my bean."

18:14.861 --> 18:17.630
My head and my heart,
they battle within,

18:17.664 --> 18:20.600
if I don't find love now,
I have to ask when

18:20.633 --> 18:23.470
will I ever find someone
as perfect as you?

18:23.503 --> 18:26.306
But that stripper has my money,
so what can we do?

18:26.339 --> 18:29.542
Please! I'm a cop with a badge,
she sells peeks at her vag.

18:29.576 --> 18:32.412
I can get all your cash,
we'll be gone in a flash.

18:32.445 --> 18:34.314
But in case we get caught,
I can't go to jail.

18:34.347 --> 18:35.715
Of course.

18:35.748 --> 18:40.753
So, the story must be
that you took me by force.

18:42.322 --> 18:43.556
[ Clank ]
[ Gasps ]

18:45.792 --> 18:47.160
[ Clanging, thud ]

18:47.194 --> 18:48.795
Now, that's a great ending.

18:48.828 --> 18:51.164
Thanks. We didn't actually do
all that rhyming at the end,

18:51.198 --> 18:52.499
but with the success
of "Hamilton,"

18:52.532 --> 18:54.534
I think I'm gonna put
that in the movie.

18:54.567 --> 18:56.203
Oh, I wouldn't.

18:56.236 --> 18:59.306
That shit is starting
to get really played out.

18:59.339 --> 19:00.707
Where's your girl?

19:00.740 --> 19:02.442
Oh, we drove about 3 miles
down the road,

19:02.475 --> 19:04.244
and I ditched her
at a truck stop.

19:04.277 --> 19:05.945
Once I was free
and had all my money,

19:05.978 --> 19:08.315
I realized her poem
kind of sucked.

19:08.348 --> 19:12.185
[ Sea birds calling ]

19:12.219 --> 19:13.720
How did you get down here?

19:13.753 --> 19:16.656
[ Mouth full ]
Mm. I drove her car. Why?

19:16.689 --> 19:18.458
Shit.

19:18.491 --> 19:19.926
You don't think they have a way
to track those, do you?

19:24.497 --> 19:26.499
Another twist.

19:26.533 --> 19:28.735
Another twist.

19:28.768 --> 19:31.904
* When I see my baby
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

19:31.938 --> 19:33.406
...with that foolishness.

19:33.440 --> 19:36.476
* What do I see?

19:36.509 --> 19:39.212
* Poetry

19:39.246 --> 19:43.583
* Poetry in motion

19:43.616 --> 19:46.719
* Poetry in motion

19:46.753 --> 19:49.922
* Walkin' by my side

19:49.956 --> 19:53.926
* Her lovely locomotion

19:53.960 --> 19:57.997
* Keeps my eyes open wide

19:58.030 --> 20:00.967
* Poetry in motion

20:01.000 --> 20:04.537
* See her gentle sway

20:04.571 --> 20:07.807
* A wave out on the ocean

20:07.840 --> 20:11.244
* Could never move that way

20:11.278 --> 20:14.947
* I love every movement

20:14.981 --> 20:18.551
* There's nothing
I would change *

20:18.585 --> 20:21.954
* She doesn't need improvement

20:21.988 --> 20:26.493
* She's much too nice
to rearrange *

20:26.526 --> 20:29.429
* Poetry in motion

20:29.462 --> 20:32.599
* Dancing close to me

20:32.632 --> 20:35.935
* A flower of devotion

20:35.968 --> 20:39.406
* A-swaying gracefully

20:39.439 --> 20:41.474
* Whoa, oh, oh

20:41.508 --> 20:46.313
* Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa-oh, whoa, oh *

20:46.346 --> 20:48.715
Hi. My name is Adam.

20:48.748 --> 20:51.418
I'm here to get the keys
to Froggy Cottage.

20:51.451 --> 20:53.686
I planned a surprise date.

20:53.720 --> 20:57.490
Ooh. Mints.

20:57.524 --> 20:59.426
Hmm. May I?

20:59.459 --> 20:59.826
Knock yourself out.

20:59.859 --> 21:01.027
Yeah?

21:01.060 --> 21:02.495
Uh-huh.
